# UI Component Skill

## 1. Decide location

| Type | Location |
|---|---|
| shadcn primitive (button, card, dialog, input, sonner, …) | `src/components/ui/` — **install via shadcn CLI**, never hand-author |
| App-aware shared composite (auth card, navigation, page shells) | `src/components/<area>/<name>.tsx` |
| Route-owned component (used only by one route) | Co-locate next to the route file: e.g., `src/routes/posts.-components/post-card.tsx` |
| Brand / app SVG icon | `src/components/icons/<name>.tsx` (named React component, accepts `className`) |

## 2. Install primitives via shadcn

```bash
yarn dlx shadcn@latest add <component>     # latest version, no pinning
```

Examples that are likely to be needed first: `button`, `card`, `dialog`, `input`, `label`, `form`, `sonner`, `dropdown-menu`, `sheet`, `tabs`. Do not introduce a different primitive library.

## 3. Author a composite

```tsx
import type { ComponentProps } from 'react'
import { cn } from '#/lib/utils'

type AuthCardProps = ComponentProps<'section'> & {
  title: string
  description?: string
}

export function AuthCard({ title, description, className, children, ...props }: AuthCardProps) {
  return (
    <section
      className={cn(
        'island-shell mx-auto w-full max-w-md rounded-2xl p-8',
        className,
      )}
      {...props}
    >
      <header className="mb-6">
        <h2 className="display-title text-2xl">{title}</h2>
        {description ? (
          <p className="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">{description}</p>
        ) : null}
      </header>
      {children}
    </section>
  )
}
```

Rules followed in the example:

- Explicit prop type, named export, kebab-case file name (`auth-card.tsx`).
- Class merge through `cn()`. Brand class `island-shell` is reused from `src/styles.css`.
- Token utilities (`text-muted-foreground`) for shadcn-aware colours.
- `ComponentProps<'section'>` to forward valid `<section>` attributes.

## 4. Variants

- Use `class-variance-authority` (`cva`) for components with multiple visual variants — it is already a dependency and matches shadcn-generated output.
- Variants and sizes are explicit props — never magic strings stitched into `className`.

## 5. Icons

- Default to `lucide-react` named imports: `import { Search } from 'lucide-react'`.
- For brand-specific glyphs, add `src/components/icons/<name>.tsx` returning inline SVG that accepts `className`.

## 6. Tests

- Colocate `<component>.test.tsx` next to the component when behaviour is testable (controlled state, handlers, conditional rendering).
- Skip tests for pure stylistic wrappers around a shadcn primitive.

## Constraints

- No business logic inside component JSX. No fetching, no router-aware logic — accept data via props or pull from the matched `Route` API at the consuming layer.
- Every interactive element has an accessible name (visible label, `aria-label`, or `aria-labelledby`).
- Don't add a dependency to satisfy a one-off icon — use `lucide-react` or an inline SVG.
- Don't hand-edit files in `src/components/ui/`; install/upgrade them via the shadcn CLI and customise via variant props.
